[
    {
        "text": "A high school student in\nfront of a laptop,",
        "start": 0.31,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "surrounded by classmates,",
        "start": 3.25,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "dressed in college gear.",
        "start": 5.03,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "A moment of\nsuspense,",
        "start": 7.13,
        "duration": 2.59
    },
    {
        "text": "and then …",
        "start": 9.72,
        "duration": 1.21
    },
    {
        "text": "[Cheers]",
        "start": 10.93,
        "duration": 3.735
    },
    {
        "text": "It was a scene repeated\nover and over again.",
        "start": 14.67,
        "duration": 3.33
    },
    {
        "text": "Students from one\nLouisiana private school",
        "start": 18.0,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "opening acceptance letters\nfrom their dream colleges.",
        "start": 20.44,
        "duration": 3.14
    },
    {
        "text": "The videos often went viral.",
        "start": 23.58,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "This one, of a\n16-year-old student",
        "start": 25.71,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "getting accepted\nto Harvard,",
        "start": 27.93,
        "duration": 1.55
    },
    {
        "text": "racked up over \n8 million views.",
        "start": 29.48,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "[Cheers]",
        "start": 31.98,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "But there was more\nto the story.",
        "start": 33.76,
        "duration": 2.12
    },
    {
        "text": "Students told us many of\ntheir college applications",
        "start": 37.22,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "included false information \nprovided by",
        "start": 39.54,
        "duration": 2.17
    },
    {
        "text": "their school’s administrators.",
        "start": 41.71,
        "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
        "text": "And the cheers in\nthese videos covered up",
        "start": 43.53,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "an ugly reality of abuse\nand intimidation",
        "start": 45.03,
        "duration": 3.23
    },
    {
        "text": "at T.M. Landry College Prep.",
        "start": 48.26,
        "duration": 1.73
    },
    {
        "text": "“Abusing emotionally, physically.",
        "start": 50.8,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "We realized, O.K.\nsomething’s not right.",
        "start": 53.38,
        "duration": 3.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Everything is wrong\nwith T.M. Landry.”",
        "start": 56.7,
        "duration": 3.1
    },
    {
        "text": "Sixteen-year-old Megan Malveaux\nis a former student.",
        "start": 61.03,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "“There was this little kid,",
        "start": 64.03,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "he was probably\nabout 7 or 8,",
        "start": 65.8,
        "duration": 3.23
    },
    {
        "text": "and he was acting up in class.",
        "start": 69.03,
        "duration": 3.95
    },
    {
        "text": "Mr. Mike, he had\ntook the kid",
        "start": 72.98,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "by the neck and\npicked him up",
        "start": 75.2,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "and body slammed\nhim on the table.”",
        "start": 77.29,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "Mr. Mike is Michael Landry.",
        "start": 79.99,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "He and his wife, Tracey,\nfounded the school.",
        "start": 82.33,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "It costs up to\n$725 a month to attend,",
        "start": 84.64,
        "duration": 3.48
    },
    {
        "text": "and received\nnational attention",
        "start": 88.12,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "for its 100 percent\ncollege acceptance rate.",
        "start": 89.89,
        "duration": 2.89
    },
    {
        "text": "In various TV interviews,",
        "start": 92.78,
        "duration": 2.11
    },
    {
        "text": "they pitched a message\nof hope and hard work.",
        "start": 94.89,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "“We’re changing society.",
        "start": 97.26,
        "duration": 2.14
    },
    {
        "text": "We’re giving hope.”",
        "start": 99.4,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go big or go home.”",
        "start": 100.78,
        "duration": 1.41
    },
    {
        "text": "The Landrys denied\nfalsifying transcripts",
        "start": 102.19,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "and college applications,",
        "start": 104.43,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "and any allegations of abuse.",
        "start": 106.03,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "But they do maintain that\nphysical punishments",
        "start": 107.99,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "are doled out",
        "start": 109.99,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "because they love their students\nand treat them like family.",
        "start": 110.99,
        "duration": 3.335
    },
    {
        "text": "The Landrys told the\nstory of young black kids",
        "start": 114.325,
        "duration": 2.755
    },
    {
        "text": "from a\nworking-class community,",
        "start": 117.08,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "who overcame systemic barriers\nto achieve success.",
        "start": 118.61,
        "duration": 3.22
    },
    {
        "text": "“Doesn’t matter who you are,",
        "start": 121.83,
        "duration": 1.23
    },
    {
        "text": "doesn’t matter where \nyou’ve been in life,",
        "start": 123.06,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "you can do it.”",
        "start": 124.99,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "And the videos were crucial\nin promoting that message.",
        "start": 126.57,
        "duration": 2.92
    },
    {
        "text": "Parents say they had no idea\nwhat was going on.",
        "start": 131.48,
        "duration": 3.1
    },
    {
        "text": "“All the videos,",
        "start": 134.58,
        "duration": 1.06
    },
    {
        "text": "I was excited for\nall the kids,",
        "start": 135.64,
        "duration": 3.47
    },
    {
        "text": "because they’re kids.",
        "start": 139.11,
        "duration": 2.84
    },
    {
        "text": "Little black kids like us",
        "start": 141.95,
        "duration": 4.429
    },
    {
        "text": "can go to Harvard, Yale.”",
        "start": 146.379,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "“I mean, the good\ntalking he did",
        "start": 149.099,
        "duration": 1.87
    },
    {
        "text": "made you realize, well, you’re\nkid needs to go to that school.",
        "start": 150.969,
        "duration": 3.73
    },
    {
        "text": "If you want the best\nfor your kid,",
        "start": 154.699,
        "duration": 1.97
    },
    {
        "text": "you need to send them\nto T.M. Landry.",
        "start": 156.669,
        "duration": 2.93
    },
    {
        "text": "You know, you speak\nto anybody in Louisiana,",
        "start": 159.599,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "they’re telling you.”",
        "start": 161.849,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "When the cameras were off,",
        "start": 162.849,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "students say they were\npitted against each other,",
        "start": 164.329,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "interrogated and humiliated.",
        "start": 166.789,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "Students say they were also\nphysically punished.",
        "start": 169.009,
        "duration": 2.27
    },
    {
        "text": "Sometimes they would\nbe forced to kneel",
        "start": 171.279,
        "duration": 2.18
    },
    {
        "text": "on rocks, rice or\nhot concrete, for hours.",
        "start": 173.459,
        "duration": 3.75
    },
    {
        "text": "“I remember the first time\nI was put on my knees",
        "start": 177.209,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "was because he gave me\na test and I failed it.”",
        "start": 179.549,
        "duration": 6.17
    },
    {
        "text": "A New York Times investigation\nfound that behind the scenes,",
        "start": 185.719,
        "duration": 3.24
    },
    {
        "text": "the Landrys filled out\ntranscripts incorrectly",
        "start": 188.959,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "to reflect classes the kids\nsay they never took",
        "start": 191.359,
        "duration": 2.81
    },
    {
        "text": "and grades they never earned.",
        "start": 194.169,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "“My transcript was\nmessed up because",
        "start": 196.79,
        "duration": 4.15
    },
    {
        "text": "he messed up my birthday\nbecause apparently",
        "start": 200.94,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "I was born the year\nmy mom was.",
        "start": 203.5,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "He put classes that I never\neven took, like chemistry.”",
        "start": 205.6,
        "duration": 5.99
    },
    {
        "text": "Students told The Times\nthat the Landrys",
        "start": 211.59,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "told them to lie on their\ncollege applications",
        "start": 213.45,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "about growing up in \nhouseholds marked by",
        "start": 216.05,
        "duration": 1.79
    },
    {
        "text": "poverty, crime\nand drug addiction.",
        "start": 217.84,
        "duration": 2.54
    },
    {
        "text": "If they refused,\nthey say the Landrys",
        "start": 220.38,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "threatened to\ndo it for them.",
        "start": 222.46,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "A look back\nreveals clues",
        "start": 224.94,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "about Michael Landry's\ntemperament,",
        "start": 226.63,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "like in this recent pitch",
        "start": 228.32,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "that became a\npassionate outburst.",
        "start": 229.8,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "[Bangs fist]",
        "start": 232.04,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "“Excuse me, ma’am.”",
        "start": 234.23,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "But this was a rare glimpse\nat his frightening tone.",
        "start": 235.45,
        "duration": 3.355
    },
    {
        "text": "The Landrys produced \na steady stream",
        "start": 238.805,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "of promotional material,",
        "start": 240.495,
        "duration": 1.73
    },
    {
        "text": "painting a positive picture \nof an unconventional school.",
        "start": 242.225,
        "duration": 2.93
    },
    {
        "text": "“T.M. Landry is\na no-frills school.”",
        "start": 245.155,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "“No classrooms,\nno walls, no books.”",
        "start": 247.945,
        "duration": 2.99
    },
    {
        "text": "“Teachers without\ncertifications.",
        "start": 250.935,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Classes with no\nteachers at all.”",
        "start": 253.095,
        "duration": 3.07
    },
    {
        "text": "After the acceptance\nvideos started",
        "start": 256.165,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "gaining traction in 2016,",
        "start": 258.105,
        "duration": 2.03
    },
    {
        "text": "press from\naround the country",
        "start": 260.135,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "started showing up at\ntheir door.",
        "start": 261.385,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "“Walking around campus,",
        "start": 262.975,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "we saw that weird\nLandry style.”",
        "start": 264.415,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "Outsiders marveled\nat how the Landrys",
        "start": 267.135,
        "duration": 2.12
    },
    {
        "text": "could make the\nimpossible happen.",
        "start": 269.255,
        "duration": 2.26
    },
    {
        "text": "“So, O.K. this is incredible.”",
        "start": 271.515,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "“The results speak\nfor themselves.”",
        "start": 272.955,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go Landrys —”",
        "start": 274.915,
        "duration": 0.689
    },
    {
        "text": "“They have figured out\nthe secret sauce —”",
        "start": 275.604,
        "duration": 1.43
    },
    {
        "text": "“They really have.”",
        "start": 277.034,
        "duration": 1.161
    },
    {
        "text": "In media interviews, they\ncalled themselves a family —",
        "start": 278.195,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "“Family first —”",
        "start": 280.715,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "that pushed kids",
        "start": 281.895,
        "duration": 1.04
    },
    {
        "text": "to their academic limits.",
        "start": 282.935,
        "duration": 1.41
    },
    {
        "text": "“They will make it. \nNo is not an option.",
        "start": 284.345,
        "duration": 2.71
    },
    {
        "text": "Failure is not an option.”",
        "start": 287.055,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Former students\nand parents told us",
        "start": 289.055,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "that for visits\nlike these, students",
        "start": 290.555,
        "duration": 1.99
    },
    {
        "text": "would be forced to\nspend days rehearsing",
        "start": 292.545,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "what to say to reporters.",
        "start": 294.635,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "“I plan to attend\nHarvard University.”",
        "start": 295.895,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "“Harvard University.”",
        "start": 297.435,
        "duration": 1.11
    },
    {
        "text": "“Stanford University.”",
        "start": 298.545,
        "duration": 1.02
    },
    {
        "text": "“Cornell.”",
        "start": 299.565,
        "duration": 0.87
    },
    {
        "text": "“Brown.”",
        "start": 300.435,
        "duration": 1.02
    },
    {
        "text": "“We have this trig book,\nwhich is like from M.I.T.,",
        "start": 301.455,
        "duration": 2.87
    },
    {
        "text": "so we just basically\nteach each other.”",
        "start": 304.325,
        "duration": 1.865
    },
    {
        "text": "For the high school students,",
        "start": 306.19,
        "duration": 1.288
    },
    {
        "text": "there was a\nsingular focus:",
        "start": 307.478,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "practicing for the ACT.",
        "start": 309.018,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "For younger kids:",
        "start": 311.098,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "a loose and\ninsufficient curriculum",
        "start": 312.098,
        "duration": 2.03
    },
    {
        "text": "that has left many\ngrade levels behind.",
        "start": 314.128,
        "duration": 3.21
    },
    {
        "text": "When their methods\nwere questioned,",
        "start": 317.338,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "the Landrys were quick\nto dismiss any suspicions.",
        "start": 318.858,
        "duration": 2.99
    },
    {
        "text": "“Some of them sound\na little brainwashed.”",
        "start": 321.848,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "“When it’s a black kid",
        "start": 323.618,
        "duration": 1.73
    },
    {
        "text": "and it’s strictly education,",
        "start": 325.348,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "something’s wrong\nwith that kid.”",
        "start": 326.878,
        "duration": 1.81
    },
    {
        "text": "“The reason why\nI never said nothing",
        "start": 329.408,
        "duration": 1.72
    },
    {
        "text": "was because I\nwas scared.",
        "start": 331.128,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "Because they were getting\nall of this attentions",
        "start": 332.958,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "from news channels.",
        "start": 336.078,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "They were in articles.",
        "start": 337.328,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "I was so brainwashed",
        "start": 339.218,
        "duration": 2.35
    },
    {
        "text": "and I was thinking,\nhe can’t do no wrong.",
        "start": 341.568,
        "duration": 3.31
    },
    {
        "text": "But as you can see\nsince I’m sitting here,",
        "start": 344.878,
        "duration": 3.94
    },
    {
        "text": "I was all wrong.”",
        "start": 348.818,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, many in the\nT.M. Landry community",
        "start": 351.188,
        "duration": 2.86
    },
    {
        "text": "say they feel swindled out of\ntime, money, and ironically,",
        "start": 354.048,
        "duration": 4.5
    },
    {
        "text": "an education.",
        "start": 358.548,
        "duration": 1.59
    }
]